# docx Skill — Word Document Creation & Manipulation

This skill provides comprehensive guidance for creating and editing Microsoft Word documents programmatically using the `docx` npm package (https://docx.js.org). Use this skill whenever you need to generate `.docx` files from Node.js code.

## Installation

```bash
npm install docx
# optional: for reading existing .docx files
npm install mammoth
```

## Core Concepts

The `docx` package uses an **immutable, declarative API**. You build a tree of objects and pass them to `Packer.toBuffer()` or `Packer.toBlob()`. Nothing is mutated after creation.

```js
const { Document, Packer, Paragraph, TextRun } = require('docx');
const fs = require('fs');

const doc = new Document({
  sections: [{
    properties: {},
    children: [
      new Paragraph({
        children: [new TextRun('Hello, World!')],
      }),
    ],
  }],
});

Packer.toBuffer(doc).then((buffer) => {
  fs.writeFileSync('output.docx', buffer);
  console.log('Document created successfully');
});
```

---

## Document Structure

A `Document` contains one or more `sections`. Each section can have its own `PageOrientation`, `PageSize`, `PageMargin`, headers, and footers.

```js
const {
  Document, Packer, Paragraph, TextRun,
  Header, Footer, PageOrientation, PageSize,
  AlignmentType, HeadingLevel,
} = require('docx');

const doc = new Document({
  title: 'My Document',
  description: 'Generated by docx',
  styles: {
    paragraphStyles: [],
  },
  sections: [
    {
      properties: {
        page: {
          size: {
            orientation: PageOrientation.LANDSCAPE,
            width: 15840, // in twips (1/20 of a point)
            height: 12240,
          },
          margin: {
            top: 720,
            right: 720,
            bottom: 720,
            left: 720,
          },
        },
      },
      headers: {
        default: new Header({
          children: [new Paragraph({ text: 'My Header' })],
        }),
      },
      footers: {
        default: new Footer({
          children: [new Paragraph({ text: 'Page Footer' })],
        }),
      },
      children: [
        new Paragraph({ text: 'Section content here' }),
      ],
    },
  ],
});
```

---

## Paragraphs

Paragraphs are the fundamental block element.

```js
const { Paragraph, TextRun, AlignmentType, HeadingLevel } = require('docx');

// Simple paragraph
new Paragraph({ text: 'Simple paragraph text' })

// Heading
new Paragraph({
  text: 'Chapter 1',
  heading: HeadingLevel.HEADING_1,
})

// Centered paragraph with mixed formatting
new Paragraph({
  alignment: AlignmentType.CENTER,
  spacing: { before: 200, after: 200 },
  children: [
    new TextRun({ text: 'Bold ', bold: true }),
    new TextRun({ text: 'and ', italics: true }),
    new TextRun({ text: 'underlined', underline: {} }),
  ],
})

// Paragraph with border
new Paragraph({
  text: 'Bordered paragraph',
  border: {
    top: { color: '000000', space: 1, style: BorderStyle.SINGLE, size: 6 },
    bottom: { color: '000000', space: 1, style: BorderStyle.SINGLE, size: 6 },
  },
})
```

### Text Formatting

```js
const { TextRun } = require('docx');

new TextRun({
  text: 'Formatted text',
  bold: true,
  italics: true,
  underline: { type: UnderlineType.SINGLE, color: 'FF0000' },
  strike: true,
  doubleStrike: false,
  subScript: false,
  superScript: true,
  color: '1F4E79',          // hex color without #
  size: 28,                  // half-points (28 = 14pt)
  font: 'Arial',
  highlight: 'yellow',
  allCaps: false,
  smallCaps: true,
  characterSpacing: 20,      // in twentieths of a point
})
```

---

## Tables

```js
const {
  Table, TableRow, TableCell, Paragraph, TextRun,
  WidthType, BorderStyle, ShadingType,
  VerticalAlign, AlignmentType,
} = require('docx');

const table = new Table({
  width: { size: 100, type: WidthType.PERCENTAGE },
  rows: [
    // Header row
    new TableRow({
      tableHeader: true,
      children: [
        new TableCell({
          children: [new Paragraph({ text: 'Name', bold: true })],
          shading: { type: ShadingType.SOLID, color: '1F4E79' },
          verticalAlign: VerticalAlign.CENTER,
          width: { size: 40, type: WidthType.PERCENTAGE },
        }),
        new TableCell({
          children: [new Paragraph({ text: 'Value', bold: true })],
          shading: { type: ShadingType.SOLID, color: '1F4E79' },
          verticalAlign: VerticalAlign.CENTER,
        }),
      ],
    }),
    // Data row
    new TableRow({
      children: [
        new TableCell({
          children: [new Paragraph({ text: 'Row 1 Col 1' })],
        }),
        new TableCell({
          children: [new Paragraph({ text: 'Row 1 Col 2' })],
        }),
      ],
    }),
  ],
  // Optional: cell spacing and margins
  layout: TableLayoutType.FIXED,
});
```

### Merged Cells (Column Span)

```js
new TableCell({
  columnSpan: 2,
  children: [new Paragraph({ text: 'Merged Cell' })],
})
```

### Row Span

```js
new TableCell({
  rowSpan: 3,
  children: [new Paragraph({ text: 'Spans 3 rows' })],
})
```

