## Error Handling

```js
try {
  const buffer = await Packer.toBuffer(doc);
  fs.writeFileSync(outputPath, buffer);
} catch (err) {
  if (err.message.includes('image')) {
    console.error('Image load error — check path and format (PNG/JPG/GIF/BMP/SVG)');
  } else {
    console.error('Document generation failed:', err.message);
  }
}
```

---

## Tips & Best Practices

1. Always specify `size` in half-points (e.g., `size: 24` = 12pt).
2. Colors are hex strings **without** the `#` prefix.
3. Measurements (margins, spacing) are in **twips** (1/20th of a point; 1440 twips = 1 inch).
4. Use `spacing.line` for line height (240 = single spacing, 480 = double spacing).
5. Images must be read as `Buffer` (Node.js) before passing to `ImageRun`.
6. For large documents, build sections incrementally and push to arrays before passing to `Document`.
7. `TableOfContents` requires the user to press Ctrl+A then F9 to refresh in Word (or use field update).

